<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-19T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-19T13:00:00-05:00" n="712" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.48/58</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-19T13:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1917, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1915. Your 2098, December 13, 10 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d712fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> Food Administration has requisitioned for France
                            flour purchased by Finnish Senate. Conditions so urgent as to offer no
                            other alternative. Department therefore arranging with Food Commission
                            for <persName corresp="#p_IK1">Ignatius</persName>, Food Commissioner of
                            Finnish Senate, now in Washington, to procure corn supplies now
                            available at Gulf ports. Will advise you later as to pork and sugar.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>